1 of the Small, Minority, and Women–Owned Businesses Account; providing that the
2 sales and use tax does not apply to the sale of certain information technology services
3 and certain digital codes and digital products under certain circumstances; altering
4 the termination date of the Build Our Future Grant Pilot Program, Job Creation Tax
5 Credit, Research and Development Tax Credit, and Employer Security Clearance
6 Costs Tax Credit; altering eligibility for and the calculation of certain tax credits;
7 allowing a qualified investor that is a pass–through entity that pays a certain income
8 tax on behalf of its members to receive and allocate in any manner a credit or refund
9 of a credit under the Biotechnology Investment Incentive Tax Credit; establishing
10 the purpose of the film production activity tax credit; authorizing a qualified film
11 production entity to amend its application for the film production activity tax credit
12 under certain circumstances; repealing altering, for certain fiscal years, a certain
13 limit on the aggregate amount of tax credit certificates that the Secretary may issue
14 for a single film production activity; altering certain reporting requirements
15 concerning certain economic development programs and tax credits; requiring the
16 Office of the Comptroller and the Department of Commerce to evaluate the film
17 production activity tax credit and submit a certain report on or before a certain date;
18 and generally relating to economic development and economic development
19 initiatives.
